hopobject.body: Have you seen any good films recently? i-med-online.de Not quite like ours. It's more that China isn't producing enough pork to keep up with its demand. With the country's booming economy, China's middle class is growing quickly and increasingly wants to buy more meat with its newfound wealth. In addition, knowing that pork is being produced and processed in the U.S. could reassure Chinese customers leery of unsafe China-produced food.
